reviews.review:
The shortest Half Life game there is, but holy hell is it fun;

Not only having a amazing plot already as a continuation of HL2 (along with pain-in-the-ass acheivements), a lot of pretty funny things happened when I played, like, No joke, I'm prreetty sure that Valve changed the ragdoll physics completly in this game. For example, a new enemy aptly named "Zombine" has strechy ragdolls which go completly wild when they land on something, and don't make that "waaaaachy" noise when the player hits them with a prop. (tried to imitate the collision noise lmao)

I HIGHLY reccomend playing the Half Life games in order, (that means you should play this game after HL2 and the prequels).
